# Documentation Location

**IMPORTANT:** All documentation files (except README.md) are located in the `docs/` directory.

When creating new documentation, place it in:
- `apps/band-positions/docs/` (for app-specific docs)

Main directory should only contain:
- README.md
- Configuration files (*.config.*, *.json, etc.)
- Source code directories (src/, public/, etc.)
- Setup scripts (setup-ios.sh, etc.)

## Current Documentation Structure

```
apps/band-positions/
├── README.md                    # Main readme (links to docs/)
├── docs/                        # All documentation here
│   ├── START_HERE.md           # Entry point
│   ├── SETUP_CHECKLIST.md      # Setup steps
│   ├── CAPACITOR_SETUP.md      # Capacitor guide
│   ├── CAPACITOR_QUICK_REF.md  # Quick reference
│   ├── ARCHITECTURE.md         # Architecture
│   ├── APP_STORE_GUIDE.md      # App Store guide
│   ├── APP_STORE_CHECKLIST.md  # App Store checklist
│   ├── XCODE_SETTINGS_GUIDE.md # Xcode settings
│   ├── WKPROCESSPOOL_WARNING.md # Warning fixes
│   ├── COCOAPODS_SCRIPT_WARNING.md
│   ├── IOS_APP_SUMMARY.md
│   └── FILES_CREATED.md
├── src/                         # Source code
├── public/                      # Static assets
└── [config files]
```
